The paper deals with distributed algorithms for shortest path problems, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of shortcuts to achieve faster running times is a technique commonly used in Networked Information Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which fall under the Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-category.
